title: 78 pianists in renowned Chopin competition in Poland
text: > Entertainment 78 pianists in renowned Chopin competition in Poland National flags of competitors from 20 nations decorate the National Philharmonic in Warsaw, Poland, Thursday, Oct. 1, 2015, the opening day of the career-paving 17th International Frederic Chopin Piano Competition that runs here through Oct. 21. Seventy-eight young pianists from around the world, out of some 450 applicants, are taking part in the competition that is held every five years and is totally dedicated to the music of the Polish composer. (AP Photo/Czarek Sokolowski)
